{"parse":{"title":"baby","pageid":3198,"redirects":[],"wikitext":"{{also|Baby}}\n==English==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{etymon|en|:inh|enm:baby|:afeq|babe|-y<id:diminutive>|tree=1}}\n{{multiple images\n|direction = vertical\n|image1 = Baby.jpg\n|caption1 = A human baby\n|image2 = Baby ginger monkey.jpg\n|caption2 = A baby [[monkey#Noun|monkey]]\n|image3 = Smaller Babyelephant45 from wiki commons.jpg\n|caption3 = A baby [[elephant]] (sometimes called a [[calf]])\n}}\n\nFrom {{inh|en|enm|baby}}, {{m|enm|babie|t=baby}}, a diminutive form of {{m|enm|babe|t=babe, baby}}, equivalent to {{suf|en|babe|y|alt2=y/-ie|t2=endearing and diminutive suffix|id2=diminutive}}. Perhaps ultimately imitative of baby talk (compare {{m|en|babble}}).<ref>{{R:Etymonline|babe}}</ref>\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{enPR|bā'bē|a=RP,GA}}, {{IPA|en|/ˈbeɪ̯.bi/}}\n* {{audio|en|En-uk-baby.ogg|a=RP}}\n* {{audio|en|en-us-baby.ogg|a=GA}}\n* {{audio|en|En-a baby.oga}}\n* {{rhymes|en|eɪbi|s=2}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{en-noun}}\n\n# A very [[young]] [[human]], particularly from [[birth]] to a couple of [[year]]s [[old]] or until [[walking]] is [[fully]] [[master]]ed.\n#* {{RQ:Tennyson In Memoriam|XLIV|67|The '''baby''' new to earth and sky,<br>⁠What time his tender palm is prest<br>⁠Against the circle of the breast,<br>Has never thought that ‘this is I:’ {{...}}}}\n#* {{quote-journal\n|en\n|date=January 19, 2017\n|author=Peter Bradshaw\n|title=T2 Trainspotting review – choose a sequel that doesn't disappoint\n|work=The Guardian\n|url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2017/jan/19/t2-trainspotting-review-ewan-mcgregor-danny-boyle-sequel\n|page=\n|passage=In that film, I often hid my head in my hands, unable to watch scenes about dead '''babies''' and diving into gruesome lavatories.}}\n## A very [[young]] [[human]], even if not yet [[born]].\n##: {{ux|en|When is your '''baby''' due?}}\n##: {{ux|en|Her '''baby''' had always been active, even before he was born, when he would kick her bladder.}}\n##* {{quote-book|en|date=2013-06-07|author=Natalie Pierce|title=Weaving My Way Through Life|publisher=Author House|isbn=9781481759120|page=44\n|text=Karen went to England to have her '''baby''' several months before he was born so he would have the medication she needed before the '''baby''' was born and she wanted the doctors she was used to when she lived there. It would be cheaper to have the '''baby''' in England. Karen named the '''baby''' Bill Joseph {{...}} He laughed a lot and loved his bath which he took in a plastic '''baby''' tub. }}\n# Any very [[young]] [[animal]], especially a [[vertebrate]]; many species have specific names for their babies, such as [[kitten]]s for the babies of [[cat]]s, [[puppy|puppies]] for the babies of [[dog]]s, and [[chick]]s for the babies of [[bird]]s. See [[:Category:Baby animals]] for more.\n# A person who is [[immature]], [[infantile]]{{,}} or [[feeble]].\n#: {{ux|en|Stand up for yourself – don't be such a '''baby'''!}}\n# A person who is [[new]] to or [[inexperienced]] in something.\n#: {{ux|en|I only qualified as an architect this summer, so I'm still a '''baby'''.}}\n# The [[lastborn]] of a [[family]]; the [[young]]est [[sibling]], [[irrespective]] of [[age]].\n#: {{ux|en|Adam is the '''baby''' of the family.}}\n#* {{quote-text|en|year=1895|author=S. R. Crockett|title=A Cry Across the Black Water\n|passage=\"You are very dull this morning, Sheriff,\" said the youngest daughter of the house, who, being the '''baby''' and pretty, had grown pettishly privileged in speech.}}\n#* {{RQ:Lindsay Redheap|page=114|passage=\"He's a year older than me.\" \"You're the '''baby''', eh?\"}}\n# A person's [[romantic partner]]; {{n-g|a term of [[endearment]] used to [[refer]] to or [[address]]}} e.g. one's [[girlfriend]], [[boyfriend]]{{,}} or [[spouse]].\n#: {{ux|en|Too busy thinking about my '''baby''', and I ain't got time for nothing else.}}\n#: {{ux|en|'''Baby''', don't cry.}}\n#* {{quote-song|en|year=1956|lyricist=Mae Boren Axton; Tommy Durden; Elvis Presley|title=w:Heartbreak Hotel|artist=w:Elvis Presley|passage=Well, since my '''baby''' left me,<br>Well, I found a new place to dwell.<br>Well, it's down at the end of Lonely Street<br>At Heartbreak Hotel.}}\n# {{lb|en|informal}} {{n-g|A form of [[address]] to a person [[consider]]ed to be [[attractive]].}}\n#: {{ux|en|Hey '''baby''', what are you doing later?}}\n# A [[thing]] that is comparatively [[small]] of its kind.\n#* {{quote-journal|en|date=2026-04-10|author=Leah Marilla Thomas|title=Here’s When Every Episode of ‘Hacks’ Season 5 Drops|journal=w:[[Cosmopolitan (magazine)|Cosmopolitan]]|url=https://www.cosmopolitan.com/entertainment/tv/a70988035/hacks-season-5-schedule/|passage=There will be only seven episodes in the final season. Previous seasons had as many as ten, nine, and eight episodes total. So this one is definitely the '''baby'''. After the season premiere, episodes will drop weekly-ish on Thursdays.}}\n# A [[concept]] or [[creation]] [[endear]]ed by its [[creator]].\n#: {{usex|en|This test program I've designed is my new '''baby'''.}}\n# A [[pet]] [[project]] or [[responsibility]].\n#: {{ux|en|You need to talk to John about that – it's his '''baby'''.}}\n#* {{quote-text|en|year=1996|author=w:Orlando Figes|title=A People's Tragedy|page=902|publisher=Folio Society|year_published=2015\n|passage=Sovnarkom was Lenin's '''baby''', it was where he focused all his energies […].}}\n# {{non-gloss|An [[affectionate]] term for anything.}}\n#: {{ux|en|See my new car here? I can't wait to take this '''baby''' for a drive.}}\n# {{lb|en|archaic}} A [[small]] [[image]] of an [[infant]]; a [[doll]].\n# {{lb|en|often|_|attributive}} One who is [[new]] to an [[identity]] or [[community]].\n#: {{ux|en|[[baby queer|'''baby''' queer]]; [[baby trans|'''baby''' trans]]}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=2020|author=Nina Kahn|title=The Joy of Hex: Modern Spells Without All the Bullsh*t|url=https://www.google.com/books/edition/The_Joy_of_Hex/_i_QDwAAQBAJ?hl=en&gbpv=1&dq=%22baby+witches%22&pg=PT56|page=unnumbered\n|passage=These more general spells and rituals can also be helpful for '''baby''' witches, who might want more time to practice before they hop into highly-specific spells.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=2020|author=Jane Kolven|title=The Holiday Detour|pageurl=https://www.google.com/books/edition/The_Holiday_Detour/DfoOEAAAQBAJ?hl=en&gbpv=1&dq=%22baby+dyke%22&pg=PT26|page=unnumbered\n|passage=That was even worse than blurting my sexuality like I had when I was what we called a “'''baby''' dyke” in college, desperate to find other lesbians for friendship or more.}}\n#* '''2021''', Yve Rees, quoted in Sam Elkin & Yve Rees, \"Spilling the T\", ''Bent Street: Australian LGBTIQA+ Arts, Writing & Ideas'', Volume 5, Issue 1, [https://www.google.com/books/edition/Bent_Street_5_1/hYs0EAAAQBAJ?hl=en&gbpv=1&dq=%22baby+trans%22&pg=PT10 unnumbered page]:\n#*: As someone who is still a ''''baby''' trans', these collaborations have taught me so much about what it means to live outside cisnormativity.\n\n====Synonyms====\n* {{sense|young human being}} {{l|en|babe}}, {{l|en|babby}}, {{l|en|babbie}}, {{l|en|infant}}, see also [[Thesaurus:baby]]\n* {{sense|young animal}} see [[Thesaurus:youngling]]\n* {{sense|immature or infantile person}} {{l|en|big baby}}\n* {{sense|term of endearment}} {{l|en|love}}, see also [[Thesaurus:sweetheart]]\n\n====Descendants====\n{{col-top|2|desc}}\n* {{desc|tpi|bebi}}\n* {{desc|cic|biibiꞌ|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|kw|babi|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|da|baby|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|nl|baby|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|fi|baby|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|fr|baby|bor=1}}\n<!-- * {{desctree|fr|bébé|bor=1}} source in [[bébé#French]] states it's probably not a borrowing from the English baby -->\n* {{desctree|de|Baby|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|afb|بيبي|tr=bēbi|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ia|baby|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|it|baby|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|ja|ベビー|ベイビー|bor=1}} \n* {{desc|pga|bebi|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|nb|baby|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|nn|baby|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|xsl|bebí|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|es|baby|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|sv|baby|bor=1}}\n* {{desc|vi|bé bi|bor=1}}\n{{col-bottom}}\n\n====Translations====\n{{multitrans|data=\n{{trans-top-see|very young human being|child}}\n* Abkhaz: {{tt|ab|аӡҟы}}\n* Afrikaans: {{tt+|af|baba}}\n* Ainu: {{tt|ain|アィアィ|tr=ayay}}\n* Akan: {{tt|ak|akokoa}}\n* Albanian: {{tt+|sq|foshnjë|f}}, {{tt+|sq|bebe|f}}\n* Aleut: {{tt|ale|aniqdux}}\n* Altai:\n*: Southern Altai: {{t|alt|бала}}\n* Amharic: {{tt|am|ሕፃን}}, {{tt|am|ማቲ}}\n* Amuzgo:\n*: Guerrero Amuzgo: {{tt|amu|lë'}}\n* Apache:\n*: Chiricahua: [[’áłchiné]] (Chiricahua); [[’éłchiné]] (Mescalero)\n*: Western Apache: {{tt|apw|mę́’}}\n* Arabic: {{tt|ar|رَضِيع|m}}\n*: Egyptian Arabic: {{tt|arz|طفل|m|tr=tefl}}, {{tt|arz|بيبي|m|tr=bebīʕ}}, {{tt|arz|نونو|m|tr=nono}}\n* Aragonese: {{t-needed|an}}\n* Aramaic:\n*: Classical Syriac: {{tt|syc|ܥܘܠܐ|tr=ʿūllā}}\n* Armenian: {{tt|hy|մանկիկ}}, {{tt+|hy|երեխա}}, {{tt+|hy|մանուկ}}\n* Aromanian: {{tt|rup|tsup|m}}, {{tt|rup|ciup|m}}, {{tt|rup|nat|m}}, {{tt|rup|beb|m}}, {{tt|rup|ficiuric|m}}, {{tt|rup|pup|m}}, {{tt|rup|pupul|m}}, {{tt|rup|poci}}, {{tt|rup|niphiu}}, {{tt|rup|njitsico}}\n* Assamese: {{tt|as|কেঁচুৱা}}\n* Asturian: {{tt+|ast|bebé|m}}, {{tt+|ast|neñu}}\n* Aymara: {{tt+|ay|wawa}}\n* Azerbaijani: {{tt+|az|körpə}}, {{tt+|az|uşaq}}\n* Bashkir: {{tt|ba|бала}}, {{tt|ba|бәләкәй бала}}, {{tt|ba|йәш бала}}, {{tt|ba|бәпәй}}, {{tt|ba|сабый}}\n* Basque: {{tt|eu|jaioberri}}\n* Belarusian: {{tt|be|дзіця́|n}}, {{tt|be|немаўля́|n}}, {{tt|be|немаўлё|n}}, {{tt|be|маладзе́нец|m}}, {{tt|be|дзіцяня́|n}}, {{tt|be|дзіцянё|n}}\n* Bengali: {{tt+|bn|শিশু}}, {{tt+|bn|বাচ্চা}}\n* Bikol:\n*: Central Bikol: {{tt+|bcl|umboy}}, {{tt+|bcl|aki}}\n* Breton: {{tt+|br|babig|m}}, {{tt+|br|poupig|m}}\n* Bulgarian: {{tt+|bg|бе́бе|n}}, {{tt+|bg|пелена́че|n}}, {{tt+|bg|кърма́че|n}}, {{t+|bg|сука́лче|n|tr=sukálče}}\n* Burmese: {{tt+|my|ကလေး}}\n* Catalan: {{tt+|ca|nadó|m}}, {{tt+|ca|bebè|m}}\n* Chamicuro: {{tt|ccc|chechakama}}\n* Chechen: {{tt|ce|бер}}\n* Cherokee: {{tt|chr|ᎤᏍᏗᎢ}}\n* Chickasaw: {{tt|cic|pushkush}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Cantonese: {{tt+|yue|BB|tr=bi4 bi1}}, {{tt|yue|蘇蝦仔|tr=sou1 haa1 zai2}}, {{tt|yue|𤘅孲仔|tr=ngaa4 ngaa1 zai2, ngaa4 aa1 zai2}}, {{tt|yue|蝦仔|tr=haa1 zai2}}, {{tt+|yue|BB仔|tr=bi1-4 bi1 zai2}}\n*: Dungan: {{tt|dng|вава}}, {{tt|dng|ва}}, {{tt|dng|щёхэр}}\n*: Eastern Min: {{tt|cdo|兒囝囝|tr=niè-giāng-giāng / niāng-giāng}}\n*: Hokkien: {{tt|nan-hbl|嬰仔|tr=iⁿ-á, eⁿ-á}}\n*: Jin: {{tt|cjy|小娃娃|tr=xiau2 va1 va1-3}}\n*: Mandarin: {{tt+|cmn|嬰兒}}, {{tt+|cmn|娃娃}}, {{tt+|cmn|小娃娃}}, {{tt+|cmn|宝宝}}, {{tt+|cmn|嬰幼兒}}, {{tt+|cmn|嬰孩}}, {{tt+|cmn|嬰|tr=yīng}} {{qualifier|literary}}\n*: Northern Min: {{tt|mnp|𤘅仔|tr=ngā-ciě}}\n*: Teochew: {{tt|nan-tws|細孥囝}}\n*: Wu: {{tt|wuu|小毛頭}}, {{tt|wuu|小小囡}}\n* Chukchi: {{tt-check|ckt|нененеӈ}}\n* Circassian:\n*: West Circassian: {{tt|ady|нану}}\n* Comanche: {{tt|com|onaa}}\n* Cornish: {{tt|kw|babi|m}}\n* Corsican: {{tt|co|ciucciu|m}}\n* Crimean Tatar: {{tt|crh|bebey}}\n* Czech: {{tt+|cs|děťátko|n}}, {{tt+|cs|miminko|n}}, {{tt+|cs|nemluvně|n}}, {{tt+|cs|kojenec|m}}\n* Danish: {{tt+|da|spædbarn|n}}, {{tt+|da|baby|c}}\n* Dutch: {{tt+|nl|baby|m}}, {{tt+|nl|zuigeling|m}}, {{tt+|nl|geborene|m|f}}, {{tt+|nl|pasgeborene|m|f}}, {{tt|nl|nieuwgeborene|m|f}}, {{tt+|nl|boreling|m}}, {{tt+|nl|wiegenkind|n}}\n* Elfdalian: {{tt|ovd|lisllislkripp|m}}\n* Esperanto: {{tt+|eo|bebo}}, {{tt+|eo|infaneto}}\n* Estonian: {{tt+|et|beebi}}, {{tt|et|rinnalaps}}, {{tt|et|imik}}\n* Faroese: {{tt|fo|pinkubarn|n}}, {{tt|fo|nýføðingur|m}}, {{tt|fo|vøggubarn|n}}, {{tt|fo|havingarbarn|n}}\n* Finnish: {{tt+|fi|vauva}} {{qualifier|not older than two years}}, {{tt+|fi|pikkulapsi}} {{qualifier|up to 5-6 years}}\n* French: {{tt+|fr|bébé|m}}\n* Frisian:\n*: West Frisian: {{tt|fy|poppe}}\n* Friulian: {{t-needed|fur}}\n* Ga: {{tt|gaa|gbeke abefaw}}\n* Galician: {{tt+|gl|bebé|m}}, {{tt+|gl|meniño|m}}, {{tt|gl|nené|m}}\n* Gallurese: {{tt|sdn|stéddu}}\n* Georgian: {{tt|ka|ბალღი}}, {{tt|ka|ჩვილი}}\n* German: {{tt+|de|Baby|n}}, {{tt+|de|Säugling|m}}, {{tt+|de|Kleinkind|n}}\n* Greek: {{tt+|e