 tire baby syndrome\n|mother and baby unit\n|nepo baby\n|nepotism baby\n|newbie\n|nigger baby\n|nonbaby\n|notch baby\n|oops baby\n|Ozempic baby\n|passport baby\n|pissbaby\n|prebaby\n|production baby\n|rainbow baby\n|red diaper baby\n|red-diaper baby\n|rubber baby buggy bumper\n|saw the baby in half\n|sexy baby voice\n|shaken baby syndrome\n|sleep like a baby\n|smooth as a baby's bottom\n|snowflake baby\n|soft as a baby's bottom\n|sooky baby\n|sow's baby\n|split the baby\n|stone baby\n|sugar baby\n|tarbaby,tar baby\n|test-tube baby\n|test tube baby\n|thalidomide baby\n|theyby\n|throw out the baby with the bath water\n|throw out the baby with the bathwater,throw the baby out with the bathwater\n|throw the baby out with the bath water\n|toilet baby\n|trust fund baby\n|unbabied\n|war baby\n|whiny-ass titty baby\n|pandemic baby\n}}\n{{lookfrom|en|baby}}\n\n===Related terms===\n* {{l|en|babe}}\n\n===See also===\n* {{l|en|child}} <!--(including babies, but includes up to age 18, or later)-->\n* {{l|en|infant}} <!--(an even earlier age)-->\n* {{l|en|toddler}} <!--(the next stage of development, when a child starts to learn to walk)-->\n\n===References===\n<references/>\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{anagrams|en|a=abby|Abby}}\n\n{{cln|en|endearing terms|terms of address}}\n{{C|en|Age|Babies|People}}\n\n==Danish==\n{{wp|da:}}\n\n===Etymology===\nBorrowed from {{bor|da|en|baby}}.\n\n===Noun===\n{{da-noun|en|er}}\n\n# A {{l|en|baby}}, an [[infant]].\n# {{lb|da|slang}} An [[attractive]] [[young]] [[female]].\n\n====Inflection====\n{{da-noun-infl|en|er}}\n\n====Synonyms====\n* {{l|da|spædbarn}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|da\n|babyalarm\n|babybio\n|babyble\n|babyblå\n|babyboom\n|babydoll\n|babydukke\n|babyface\n|babyfløjl\n|babylem\n|babylift\n|babylyserød\n|babymad\n|babymajs\n|babymassage\n|babypudder\n|babysitning\n|babysitte\n|babysitter\n|baby-sitter\n|babysitting\n|babysko\n|babysnak\n|babysprog\n|babysvømning\n|babysæl\n|babytøj\n|babyudstyr\n|babyvræl\n}}\n\n==Dutch==\n\n===Etymology===\nBorrowed from {{bor|nl|en|baby}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|nl|/ˈbeːbi/}}\n* {{audio|nl|Nl-baby.ogg}}\n* {{hyphenation|nl|ba|by}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{nl-noun|m|-'s|+}}\n\n# {{l|en|baby}} {{gloss|infant}}\n#: {{syn|nl|zuigeling}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|nl\n|babyachtig\n|babyboom\n|babyface\n|babyfoon\n|babyfoto\n|babykleding\n|babykleren\n|babyluier\n|babypoeder\n|babyshampoo\n|couveusebaby\n}}\n\n{{C|nl|Babies}}\n\n==Finnish==\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alter|fi|beibi|beibe}}\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{bor|fi|en|baby}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{fi-p|beibi[ba.by]|beibe|baby|q3=rare}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{fi-noun}}\n\n# [[#English|baby]] {{gloss|term of endearment}}\n#: {{syn|fi|Thesaurus:kultanen}}\n# {{lb|fi|rare|_|outside compounds}} {{synonym of|fi|vauva||baby}} {{gloss|very young human}}\n\n====Declension====\nThis spelling should preferably be used in nominative only as it does not fit into any standard inflection scheme.\n{{fi-decl-valo|bab|||y|ä}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:fi:KTSK|accessdate=2023-07-02}}\n\n==French==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{bor+|fr|en|baby}}, from {{der|fr|enm|baby}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{fr-IPA|bebby}}\n* {{audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-LoquaxFR-baby.wav|a=<<France>> (<<Vosges>>)}}\n* {{audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-WikiLucas00-baby (à l'anglaise).wav|a=<<France>> (<<Lyon>>)}}\n* {{audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-WikiLucas00-baby (babi).wav|a=<<France>> (<<Lyon>>)}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{fr-noun|m}}\n\n# [[table soccer]], [[table football]]\n# {{l|en|baby}}, [[darling]], [[sweetheart]]\n# [[Mary Jane]] shoes\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:fr:TLFi}}\n\n==Interlingua==\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|ia|noun}}\n\n# [[#English|baby]]\n\n====Synonyms====\n* {{l|ia|bebe}}\n\n==Italian==\n{{wp|it:}}\n\n===Etymology===\n{{ubor|it|en|baby}}.<ref>{{R:it:Trec}}</ref>\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{it-pr|bèbi<r:DiPI<<name:dipi>>><hyph:bà.by>|!bébi<r:<<name:dipi>>><hyph:bà.by>}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{it-noun|mfbysense|#}}\n\n# {{lb|it|uncommon}} [[child]], {{l|en|baby}}, [[neonate]]\n# {{lb|it|vocative|sometimes|jocular}} {{l|en|baby}}, [[babe]], [[darling]]\n\n===Noun===\n{{it-noun|m|#}}\n\n# a small [[shot]] of [[whisky]]\n# [[tripod]] for a film camera\n\n===Adjective===\n{{it-adj|inv=1}}\n\n# [[early]], [[anticipated]]\n# made up of [[minor]]s\n#: {{uxi|it|[[baby gang]]|youth gang(s)}}\n# pertaining to [[young]] [[children]]; for [[use]] by young children\n#: {{uxi|it|[[baby parking]]|[[childcare]] {{q|place}}}}\n# very [[young]]\n#: {{uxi|it|[[baby soldato]]|child soldier(s)}}\n\n===References===\n{{reflist}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:it:Trec|type=sinonimi}}\n\n==Lower Sorbian==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|dsb|/ˈbabɨ/}}\n\n===Etymology 1===\nFrom {{bor|dsb|de|Baby}}, from {{der|dsb|en|baby}}.\n\n====Noun====\n{{dsb-noun|m-an,n}}\n\n# [[#English|baby]] {{gl|infant}}\n#: {{syn|dsb|góletko}}\n\n=====Declension=====\nAs a masculine noun:\n{{dsb-decl-noun|<!--\nnom.sg.--> baby|<!--nom.du.--> babyja|<!--nom.pl.--> babyje|<!--\ngen.sg.--> babyja|<!--gen.du.--> babyjowu|<!--gen.pl.--> babyjow|<!--\ndat.sg.--> babyjoju|<!--dat.du.--> babyjoma|<!--dat.pl.--> babyjam|<!--\nacc.sg.--> babyja|<!--acc.du.--> babyjowu|<!--acc.pl.--> [[babyje]], [[babyjow]]|<!--\nins.sg.--> babyjom|<!--ins.du.--> babyjoma|<!--ins.pl.--> babyjami|<!--\nloc.sg.--> babyju|<!--loc.du.--> babyjoma|<!--loc.pl.-->babyjach}}\nAs a neuter noun, indeclinable.\n\n===Etymology 2===\n{{nonlemma}}\n\n====Noun====\n{{head|dsb|noun form}}\n\n# {{infl of|dsb|baba||gen|s|;|nom//acc|p}}\n\n{{C|dsb|Babies}}\n\n==Middle English==\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alter|enm|babee|babi|babie}}\n\n===Etymology===\n{{etymon|enm|:af|babe|-y<id:diminutive><ety:inh<ang:-iġ<id:diminutive>>>}}\nFrom {{af|enm|babe|-y}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|enm|/ˈbaːbiː/|/ˈbabiː/}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|enm|noun}}\n\n# {{tlb|enm|rare}} A [[child]] or {{l|en|baby}}.\n\n====Descendants====\n* {{desc|en|baby|babby|alts=1}} {{see desc}}\n* {{desc|sco|babbie}}\n\n====References====\n* {{R:MED Online|bābe|n|MED3369}}\n\n{{C|enm|Babies|Children}}\n\n==Norwegian Bokmål==\n{{wp|no:Spedbarn}}\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{der|nb|en|baby}}.\n\n===Noun===\n{{nb-noun-m1}}\n\n# a {{l|en|baby}}\n\n====Synonyms====\n* {{l|nb|spedbarn}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n* {{l|nb|babymat}}\n* {{l|nb|babyolje}}\n\n===References===\n* {{R:nb:OB}}\n\n==Norwegian Nynorsk==\n{{wp|nn:Spedbarn}}\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{der|nn|en|baby}}.\n\n===Noun===\n{{nn-noun-m1}}\n\n# a {{l|en|baby}}\n\n====Synonyms====\n* {{l|nn|spedbarn}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n* {{l|nn|babymat}}\n* {{l|nn|babyolje}}\n\n===References===\n* {{R:nn:OB}}\n\n==Polish==\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|pl|noun form|g=f}}\n\n# {{inflection of|pl|baba||gen|s|;|nom//acc//voc|p}}\n\n==Slovak==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{sk-IPA}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|sk|noun form}}\n\n# {{inflection of|sk|baba||gen|s|;|nom//acc|p}}\n\n==Spanish==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{ubor|es|en|baby}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n{{es-pr|beibi|hyph=+}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{es-noun|m}}\n\n# {{l|en|baby}}\n# {{lb|es|Dominican Republic|Venezuela|Colombia|Puerto Rico|Cuba|slang|colloquial|chiefly|reggaeton}} [[girl]], [[love]]\n\n====Usage notes====\n{{es-unadapted}}\n\n==Swedish==\n{{wikipedia|lang=sv}}\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{audio|sv|Sv-en baby.ogg}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{sv-noun|c}}\n\n# a {{l|en|baby}} (very young human)\n#: {{syn|sv|bebis|q1=more common|spädbarn|q2=more formal}}\n\n====Usage notes====\nUncommon outside compounds, especially in the plural. The plural \"babies\" mentioned in SO is likely to be seen as [[Swenglish]] in modern times.\n\n====Declension====\n{{sv-decl-noun|baby|babyn|[[babys]], [[babies]]|-|babys|babyns|[[babys]], [[babies]]|-}}\n\n===References===\n* {{R:svenska.se|so}}\n* {{R:svenska.se|saol}}"}}